# Work-scoped branches

Before substantive implementation (anything beyond a one-line typo the user explicitly names), **create a dedicated branch** from the agreed base (usually `main`, or the branch the user specifies).

## Naming

Use: **`<scope>/<short-kebab-description>`** (lowercase, hyphens).

## Scopes (pick one primary scope per branch)

| Scope | Use for |
|-------|---------|
| `knowledge-graph/` | `docs/lat.md` wiki, wikilink graph, `docs/knowledge-graph-view/`, parser, tests, `graph:view` / `graph:check` |
| `platform/` | CI, git hooks, `package.json` scripts, TypeScript/Vitest config, repo automation |
| `docs/` | Documentation outside the lat graph when it is the main change |
| `feat/` | Product features (application behavior) when not covered above |
| `fix/` | Bug fixes |
| `chore/` | Mechanical maintenance only when no scope above fits |

Keep **one coherent class of work** per branch. Split unrelated changes.

## Examples

- `knowledge-graph/expose-graph-json-api`
- `platform/pre-push-verify-tuning`
- `feat/org-model-ingest-endpoint`
